opological index and prove the equality with the analytic-Fredholm\nindex, and use it to get a cohomological index formula for every fully elliptic\noperator. In particular, for a perturbed family of generalized Dirac operators\nwe can compare our formula with the one by Melrose-Piazza to get a new\ngeometric expression for the eta form of the family.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Nov 2017 02:48:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Jan 2018 10:46:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Jul 2018 13:23:17 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 14 Apr 2021 11:18:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-15"}
